messages.message: No updates yet - I've been too busy with S3 IAM roles work

There was a short time where we did allow decimals, but then we changed it back due to feedback (https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C05EQQJGN7L/p1713888178212399?thread_ts=1713885524.756309&cid=C05EQQJGN7L). The assumption is that if our confidence values are accurate, then the precision of decimal values isn't particularly meaningful
If anything here is a bug, it's that we allow decimals between 0.1 to 0.9 rather than force it to be 0 or 1. Are we definitely changing it to allow decimals now?
